column3: Alisaie has only one thing on her mind.
Speak with Alisaie at Maelstrom Command.
Alas, the Ironworks crew couldn't linger long─far too much to do. Yet brief though our time together was, it was <Emphasis>bloody</Emphasis> good to see them!
At long last, we have our cure...
In theory, at any rate. We cannot be certain until such time as we put it to the proof, but I am quietly confident.
Well, if we're to test it on someone, then I suggest Ga Bu. His symptoms are relatively mild.
It'll be fine, I'm sure of it.
As long as you exercise due caution...
Yes. As long as we exercise due caution, it will be fine.
Without further ado, then, let's make for Limsa. We've kept Ga Bu waiting long enough!
I doubt I could contribute much towards what comes next, so I shall cheer you on from afar. Best of luck with the treatment.
We'll all be praying for your success!
'Tis plain Alisaie is very fond of Ga Bu. To the extent that I have a hand in it, I shall do all in my power to bring him back.
Well, this is the moment of truth. I'll have our hosts bring Ga Bu to us at once.
Alisaie will succeed, I am certain of it. We need but have faith.
Well, this seems as good a spot as any to have a rest.
